{"word":"G2040 - ἐργάτης - ergátēs - er-gat'-ace - Labourer","slug":"G2040","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἐργάτης</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ergátēs"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>er-gat'-ace"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Labourer"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"- Original: <b><el>ἐργάτης</el></b> <p />- Transliteration: <b>Ergates</b> <p />- Phonetic: <b>er-gat'-ace</b> <p class=\"def\">- Definition: </p> <p class='li260'><b>1.</b> a workman, a labourer </p> <p class='li520'><b>a.</b> usually one who works for hire esp. an agricultural worker </p> <p class='li260'><b>2.</b> one who does, a worker, perpetrator </p> <p class=\"origin\"/>- Origin: from <a href=\"#/G2041\">G2041</a> <p />- TDNT entry: 12:35,3 <p />- Part(s) of speech: Noun Masculine <p />- Strong's: From <a href=\"#/G2041\">G2041</a>; a <i>toiler</i>; figuratively a <b><i>teacher</i></b>: - labourer worker (-men). "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1753\">G1753</a>, <a href=\"#/G1754\">G1754</a>, <a href=\"#/G1755\">G1755</a>, <a href=\"#/G1756\">G1756</a>, <a href=\"#/G2038\">G2038</a>, <a href=\"#/G2039\">G2039</a>, <a href=\"#/G2041\">G2041</a>, <a href=\"#/G2108\">G2108</a>, <a href=\"#/G2109\">G2109</a>, <a href=\"#/G2110\">G2110</a>"}]}